      "message": "Thanks for the submission!\nI have made some change suggestions.\n- yang part is missing, could you please add it ? I have provided a suggestion\n- I would prefer to avoid definig \u0027legacy-like\u0027 user input and directly target 2 definitions: for the interface: total_loss is scalar, total_loss_per_frequency is a list of dict. This simplifies a lot the patch (no conversion yang-legacy needed). In the core, total loss can behave the same as loss_coef.\n\nPlease see the details in the comments.",
