      "side": 1,
      "message": "total_loss_per_frequency also needs a definition in yang model. This is also a way to ensure that if total_loss_per_frequency is defined, there should not be any other definition for loss.\nsomthing like: \n\n    choice loss_coef-vector-or-scalar {\n      mandatory true;        \u003c- ensure that at least one of these cases must be implemented\n      description\n        \"Loss coef definition: scalar or per frequency vector\";\n      case scalar {...}\n      ...\n      case total_loss_vector {\n        list total_loss_per_frequency {\n          key frequency;\n          min-elements 2;\n          description\n            \"Per frequency loss_coef definition.\";\n          leaf frequency {\n            type decimal64 {\n              fraction-digits 1;\n            }\n            units \"Hz\";\n            description\n              \"Frequency of the loss coef value.\";\n          }\n          leaf total_loss_value {\n            type decimal64 {\n              fraction-digits 6;\n            }\n            units \"dB\";\n            description\n              \"Loss at the frequency value.\";\n          }\n        }\n      }\n      case total_loss_scalar {\n        leaf total_loss {\n          type decimal64 {\n            fraction-digits 3;\n          }\n          units \"dB\";\n          description\n            \"Loss of the fiber span.\";\n        }\n      }\n\nand the precision dict must be updated accordinglygnpy/yang/precision_dict.py, \n    \"total_loss_value\": 6, \"total_loss\": 6,",
