      "writtenOn": "2026-02-20T13:39:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "to be yang compliant (the target is to progressively remove legacy formats), I suggest to define 2 parameters: total_loss for the scalar case and total_loss_per_frequency for the array case, and avoid the conversion.. So total_loss can only be a scalar (verified with yang) and total_loss_per_frequency can only be an list of dict with at least 2 items",
      "revId": "c93cd88fdc59298526edec73a4d92360446e2cd3",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
