        "id": 1017751
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-02-20T13:39:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this would change to something like:\n\n            if \u0027total_loss\u0027 in kwargs:\n                self._total_loss \u003d asarray(kwargs[\u0027total_loss\u0027])\n                self._f_loss_ref \u003d asarray(self._ref_frequency)  # Hz\n                self._loss_coef \u003d asarray(self._total_loss / (self._length * 1e-3)) * 1e-3  # dB/m\n            elif \u0027total_loss_per_frequency\u0027 in kwargs:\n                # Frequency-dependent total loss: list of frequency-value\n                self._total_loss \u003d asarray([v[\u0027total_loss_value\u0027] for v in kwargs[\u0027total_loss_per_frequency\u0027]])  # dB\n                self._f_loss_ref \u003d asarray([v[\u0027frequency\u0027] for v in kwargs[\u0027total_loss_per_frequency\u0027]])  # Hz\n                self._loss_coef \u003d self._total_loss / (self._length * 1e-3)  # dB/km -\u003e dB/m (*1e-3)\n                self._loss_coef \u003d self._loss_coef * 1e-3  # dB/m\n            elif \u0027loss_coef\u0027 in kwargs and isinstance(kwargs[\u0027loss_coef\u0027], dict):\n                self._loss_coef \u003d asarray(kwargs[\u0027loss_coef\u0027][\u0027value\u0027]) * 1e-3  # lineic loss dB/m\n                self._f_loss_ref \u003d asarray(kwargs[\u0027loss_coef\u0027][\u0027frequency\u0027])  # Hz\n            else:\n                self._loss_coef \u003d asarray(kwargs[\u0027loss_coef\u0027]) * 1e-3  # lineic loss dB/m\n                self._f_loss_ref \u003d asarray(self._ref_frequency)  # Hz\n                \nno need to cascade multiple if/else: the yang validation takes care of the data quality.",
      "revId": "c93cd88fdc59298526edec73a4d92360446e2cd3",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
